==Spanish==
===Etymology===
latin ''[[tripaliare]]'' - ''[[tripalium]]'': a medieval instrument of torture made by three (tri) crossed sticks ([[palium]]). So, the spanish work is rather a punisment than the action that gives man dignity. Farmer's work, however, is ''[[labrar]]'', a more grateful expression..., !but not  nowadays¡.

